{{Quote|I've done many other video games, including 3 or 4 Star Wars Games, PGA golf with Tiger Woods, 9 characters in Lord of the Rings&hellip; every job is fun, but Nintendo is number one!|Charles Martinet|<ref name="SWTweet">{{Twitter|CharlesMartinet|status/1266754523885965313|Charles Martinet|archivedate=20200530162619}}</ref>}}
'''Charles Martinet''' is an [[Wikipedia:Americans|American]]<ref name="FB" /> voice actor born on [[September 17]],<ref name="Birthdate" /> [[1950s#1955|1955]],<ref name="Birthyear" /> in [[Wikipedia:California|Califonia]],<ref name="Birthlocation" /> [[Wikipedia:United States|United States]],<ref name="United States" /> who is well known for voicing [[Wikipedia:Nintendo|Nintendo]] protagonist [[Wikipedia:Mario|Mario]] and other characters in the [[Wikipedia:Super Mario|''Super Mario'']] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] series.<ref name="Guinness" /> He has voiced various supporting characters in ''[[Star Wars]]'' video games published by [[LucasArts]], beginning with the role of [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Garreth Holtz]] in [[1999]]'s ''[[Star Wars: X-Wing Alliance]]''.<ref name="X-Wing">''[[Star Wars: X-Wing Alliance]]''</ref> In [[2001]], he voiced [[2-1B surgical droid/Legends|2-1B surgical droids]], [[Vehicle Command Crewer|AT-AT drivers]], and the [[B1-series battle droid]] [[OOM-9/Legends|OOM-9]] in ''[[Star Wars: Galactic Battlegrounds]]''.<ref name="Galactic Battlegrounds">''[[Star Wars: Galactic Battlegrounds]]''</ref> In ''[[Star Wars: Jedi Knight II: Jedi Outcast]]'', released in [[2002]], Martinet voiced [[Bespin Wing Guard/Legends|Bespin cop]] 2, a civilian [[Gender/Legends|male]], [[Imperial officer/Legends|Imperial officer]] 2,<ref name="Jedi Outcast">''[[Star Wars: Jedi Knight II: Jedi Outcast]]''</ref> and Rebel shock troop 3.<ref name="Outcast manual">''[[Star Wars: Jedi Knight II: Jedi Outcast]]'' manual</ref>

